MALAYSIA DAYBOOK: Top Glove Earnings, Berjaya Sports Profit

-- B y   B a r r y   P o r t e r
-- 
2011-03-15T21:20:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/malaysia-daybook-top-glove-earnings-berjaya-sports-profit.html
Top Glove Corp. (TOPG MK), the
world’s biggest rubber-glove maker, will announce second-quarter
earnings during the 12:30 p.m. break. Its profit dropped in each
of the past two quarters, reflecting higher latex costs and a
weaker  U.S. dollar .  WHAT TO WATCH:
* TMC Life Sciences Bhd. (TMCL MK) will sign an agreement with
Bank Riau Kepri of Sumatra at 12 p.m.
* Berjaya Sports Toto Bhd. (MSTY MK) 3Q net income rose 17.3% to
114.9 million ringgit ($37 million).
* Brem Holding Bhd. (BREM MK) agreed to buy industrial land from
Roca  Malaysia  Sdn. for 48 million ringgit.
* Ranhill Bhd. (RANH MK) denied a Business Times report saying
it faced cost overruns on a housing project it suspended in
Libya.
* Scientex Inc. (SCI MK) said second-quarter net income rose 47%.
* Sunchirin Industries (Malaysia) Bhd. (SCR MK), a Malaysian
automobile components maker, will invest 40 million ringgit this
year to expand its Thai operations.  MARKETS:
* Malaysia’s FTSE Bursa Malaysia KLCI Index fell 0.8 percent.
* The MSCI Asia Pacific Index dropped 5 percent.
* The  Dow Jones Industrial Average  lost 1.2 percent.
* Palm oil May-delivery futures advanced 1.5 percent to 3,385
ringgit a metric ton.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Barry Porter in  Kuala Lumpur  at 
 bporter10@bloomberg.net  